daryAttribute":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","Choices":{"2":{"Display":"Not valuable at all"},"3":{"Display":"Of almost no value"},"4":{"Display":"A little valuable"},"5":{"Display":"Somewhat valuable"},"7":{"Display":"Moderately valuable"},"8":{"Display":"Very valuable"},"9":{"Display":"Extremely valuable"}},"ChoiceOrder":["2","3","4","5","7","8","9"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":10,"NextAnswerId":3,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","RecodeValues":{"2":"1","3":"2","4":"3","5":"4","7":"5","8":"6","9":"7"},"DataExportTag":"Q560","QuestionID":"QID560"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID567","SecondaryAttribute":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","Choices":{"2":{"Display":"Not valuable at all"},"3":{"Display":"Of almost no value"},"4":{"Display":"A little valuable"},"5":{"Display":"Somewhat valuable"},"7":{"Display":"Moderately valuable"},"8":{"Display":"Very valuable"},"9":{"Display":"Extremely valuable"}},"ChoiceOrder":["2","3","4","5","7","8","9"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":10,"NextAnswerId":3,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"How valuable is this lesson to you?","RecodeValues":{"2":"1","3":"2","4":"3","5":"4","7":"5","8":"6","9":"7"},"DataExportTag":"Q567","QuestionID":"QID567"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID13","SecondaryAttribute":"In 2001, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but decided the rival company\u2019s market was laugh.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"In 2001, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but decided the rival company\u2019s market was laughably niche. Come 2011, Netflix was worth 13 billion, and perhaps because of their decision, Blockbuster was bankrupt.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"sp.bg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In 2001, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but decided the rival company\u2019s market was laugh...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID13"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID221","SecondaryAttribute":"In 2016, Jean-Philippe Courtois was put in charge of Microsoft\u2019s global sales and operations (ove.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>In 2016, Jean-Philippe Courtois was put in charge of Microsoft\u2019s global sales and operations (over 40,000 people) as the company shifted to cloud based software. To best accommodate this change, Courtois decided to replace the company\u2019s training on anticipating customer questions with training on listening to customers, and scrapped lengthy performance reviews for coaching opportunities on interpersonal skills. Despite a huge transition to a cloud-based infrastructure, Microsoft saw a $19 million rise in revenue from 2016 to 2018 \u2013 mostly thanks to satisfied customers.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"In 2016, Jean-Philippe Courtois was put in charge of Microsoft\u2019s global sales and operations (ove...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.\n<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q221","QuestionID":"QID221"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID14","SecondaryAttribute":"Late in post-production for Jurassic Park, director Steven Spielberg cut top-quality stop-motion...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Late in post-production for Jurassic Park, director Steven Spielberg cut top-quality stop-motion models of the dinosaurs to try never-before-used computer generated renderings. This risky change may have helped the movie to break box office records.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"sp.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Late in post-production for Jurassic Park, director Steven Spielberg cut top-quality stop-motion...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID14"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID259","SecondaryAttribute":"Listen to the patient; they are telling you the diagnosis.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Listen to the patient; they are telling you the diagnosis.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Listen to the patient; they are telling you the diagnosis.","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q259","QuestionID":"QID259"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID36","SecondaryAttribute":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now how much do you think the above taught you?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"t.n2","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Nothing"},"2":{"Display":"A lot"}},"QuestionID":"QID36"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID43","SecondaryAttribute":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now how much do you think the above taught you?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Nothing"},"2":{"Display":"A lot"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now how much do you think the above taught you?","DataExportTag":"t.g2","QuestionID":"QID43"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID608","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle ma...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. <\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle ma...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q608","QuestionID":"QID608"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID664","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle ma...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same case study on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle ma...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q664","QuestionID":"QID664"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID599","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling e...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same case study on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling e...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q599","QuestionID":"QID599"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID656","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling e...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same case study on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same case study on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling e...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q656","QuestionID":"QID656"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID605","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged. The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. An employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThe damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. \r\nAn employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q605","QuestionID":"QID605"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID611","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<br><\/b><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged. They solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThey solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q611","QuestionID":"QID611"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID662","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged. The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. An employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThe damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. \r\nAn employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q662","QuestionID":"QID662"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID666","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged. They solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.\n<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found th...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThey solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q666","QuestionID":"QID666"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID593","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 im...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 im...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q593","QuestionID":"QID593"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID648","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 im...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<br><\/b><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 im...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q648","QuestionID":"QID648"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID596","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove t...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove t...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q596","QuestionID":"QID596"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID658","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove t...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same lesson on three more scales. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove t...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q658","QuestionID":"QID658"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID602","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Companies that package their products in w...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same message on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Companies that package their products in w...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q602","QuestionID":"QID602"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID660","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Companies that package their products in w...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same message on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Companies that package their products in w...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q660","QuestionID":"QID660"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID590","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling evid...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same message on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling evid...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q590","QuestionID":"QID590"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID625","SecondaryAttribute":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling evid...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now please rate the same message on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now please rate the same message on three more scales. Even if you have extremely compelling evid...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Now please rate the same message on three more scales.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q625","QuestionID":"QID625"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID84","SecondaryAttribute":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the information. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the information. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.","DataExportTag":"Q84","QuestionID":"QID84"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID331","SecondaryAttribute":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The information you were shown derives from this case study:<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q331","QuestionID":"QID331"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID378","SecondaryAttribute":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>Dettol was a trusted antiseptic brand looking to expand. Because of this, they introduced over 8 new products, including soap, shaving cream, floor cleaner, talcum powder, mouthwash, handwash, moisturizer, and sunscreen. Only the soap and handwash were successful, with the rest of the products hovering between 0.5% and 5% market share. Dettol could have prevented this poor investment by recognizing that people only associated the brand as being \u201ca germ killer,\u201d and \u201cdoctor\u2019s choice.\u201d<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q378","QuestionID":"QID378"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID384","SecondaryAttribute":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>Merrick created a pet food that reduced plaque. In their packaging, they advertised that the product would ensure pets had \u201cclean teeth.\u201d However, consumer reports showed that 54% - 59% of customers were interested instead in foods that created \u201cfresh breath.\u201d Because of this small discrepancy, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q384","QuestionID":"QID384"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID390","SecondaryAttribute":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>In 2007, A Korean telecommunications company wanted to make an expensive move from 2G to 3G, but 3G only offered video-calling, roaming, and slightly higher speed data over competitors. To generate customer interest, they branded 3G around these features as \u201cthe key to fun.\u201d Accordingly, they released a teaser ad called \u201cDeath of Boredom,\u201d recolored their stores in bright orange and white, and did a promotion with a major movie theater chain. As a result, the 3G transition brought 8.7 times the ad impact of its competitors, and increased their profits by $450 million in just 2007, despite pouring $2.8 billion into marketing.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>Now that you've had a moment to reflect on what exactly you learned, we'd like you to rerate the case. You are welcome to respond in the same way or change your answers from before.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q390","QuestionID":"QID390"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID37","SecondaryAttribute":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"a.n2","QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Very much so"}},"QuestionID":"QID37"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID44","SecondaryAttribute":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"Slider","Selector":"HSLIDER","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","CSSliderMin":0,"CSSliderMax":100,"GridLines":0,"SnapToGrid":false,"NumDecimals":"0","ShowValue":false,"CustomStart":true,"SliderStartPositions":{"1":0.4981167608286252157512308258446864783763885498046875},"NotApplicable":false,"MobileFirst":true},"QuestionDescription":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"~"}},"ChoiceOrder":[1],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":2,"NextAnswerId":3,"Labels":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Very much so"}},"QuestionText_Unsafe":"Now to what extent would you be able to apply the knowledge offered above to other situations?","DataExportTag":"a.g2","QuestionID":"QID44"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID322","SecondaryAttribute":"Now, let's consider the other extreme. Try to remember one of the least interesting lessons you'v...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Now, let's consider the other extreme. <br><br>Try to remember one of the <i>least interesting lessons<\/i><b style=\"\"> <\/b>you've ever received -- again it could be from an article, video, class, or relative. This lesson could have taught you a lot, but nevertheless was incredibly boring or uncompelling. This kind of lesson should get a \"Not at all\" on the scale below.&nbsp;Please fill out the scale accordingly.<br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q322","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now, let's consider the other extreme. Try to remember one of the least interesting lessons you'v...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID322"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID125","SecondaryAttribute":"Now, please rate the bolded information above.","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Now, please rate the bolded information above.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q125","QuestionID":"QID125","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Now, please rate the bolded information above.","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID329","SecondaryAttribute":"Overall, did you learn more from the message or the case it came from?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Overall, did you learn more from the message or the case it came from?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"cvm","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Overall, did you learn more from the message or the case it came from?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"message"},"2":{"Display":"case"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":5,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID329"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID75","SecondaryAttribute":"Overall, which statement do you find more insightful?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Overall, which statement do you find more insightful?","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"choice","QuestionID":"QID75","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Overall, which statement do you find more insightful?","Choices":{"4":{"Display":"In 2000, Blockbuster had a chance to buy Netflix but thought the rival company\u2019s market was laughably niche. Come 2011, Netflix was worth 13 billion, and because of their decision, Blockbuster was bankrupt."},"5":{"Display":"Companies, corporations, or industries that do not have the foresight to anticipate future consumer desires and preferences will always find themselves pushing outdated products and unable to turn a profit."}},"ChoiceOrder":["4","5"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":7,"NextAnswerId":1,"Randomization":{"Advanced":null,"Type":"All","TotalRandSubset":""}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID38","SecondaryAttribute":"Please enter your unique prolific ID below","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please enter your unique prolific ID below","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"id","QuestionID":"QID38","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Please enter your unique prolific ID below","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID33","SecondaryAttribute":"Please explain what additional information is provided by the statement chose (in comparison to t...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Please explain what additional information is provided by the statement chose (in comparison to the other).","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"qual","QuestionType":"TE","Selector":"SL","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"Que