e did not.","Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"MinChar","MinChars":"30"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"SearchSource":{"AllowFreeResponse":"false"},"DisplayLogic":{"0":{"0":{"ChoiceLocator":"q:\/\/QID329\/SelectableChoice\/2","Description":"<span class=\"ConjDesc\">If<\/span> <span class=\"QuestionDesc\">Overall, did you learn more from the message or the case it came from?<\/span> <span class=\"LeftOpDesc\">case<\/span> <span class=\"OpDesc\">Is Selected<\/span> ","LeftOperand":"q:\/\/QID329\/SelectableChoice\/2","LogicType":"Question","Operator":"Selected","QuestionID":"QID329","QuestionIDFromLocator":"QID329","QuestionIsInLoop":"no","Type":"Expression"},"Type":"If"},"Type":"BooleanExpression","inPage":false}}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID4","SecondaryAttribute":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking technologies contributes to the financial, critical, and cultural success of the cinematic production in which those new technologies were utilized.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"gd.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID4"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID8","SecondaryAttribute":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking technologies could perhaps contribute to the financial, critical, and cultural success of the movie in which those new technologies were utilized.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"gp.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID8"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID11","SecondaryAttribute":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking technologies contributes to the financial, critical, and cultural success of the cinematic production in which those new technologies were utilized.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"sd.gg","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"Risking experimentation with and (ultimately) implementation of novel, still untested filmmaking...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID11"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID228","SecondaryAttribute":"The Edwards family pooled $35,000 of their own money to produce their homeopathic cure for consti...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>The Edwards family pooled $35,000 of their own money to produce their homeopathic cure for constipation: the Squatty Potty. With no money left to market the Potty, the family decided to simply give it away to various health media influencers on Instagram, Facebook, and Twitter. Despite spending no money on advertising, sales of the product quickly rose to $28,000, and caught the attention of Dr. Oz, Howard Stern, and Shark Tank, bringing Squatty Potty to an annual revenue of $12 million.<\/i>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The Edwards family pooled $35,000 of their own money to produce their homeopathic cure for consti...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.\n<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i>","DataExportTag":"Q228","QuestionID":"QID228"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID151","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with a real-world case study.","DataExportTag":"Q151","QuestionID":"QID151"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID220","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor.<br><br>The instructor gave this real-world case study.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor.<br><br>The instructor gave this real-world case study.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q220","QuestionID":"QID220"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID227","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor.<br><br>The instructor gave this real-world case study.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor.<br><br>The instructor gave this real-world case study.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q227","QuestionID":"QID227"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID273","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q273","QuestionID":"QID273"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID303","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. The instructor...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q303","QuestionID":"QID303"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID134","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with this real-world case study:","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with a real-world case study.","DataExportTag":"Q134","QuestionID":"QID134"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID167","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor opened with the following message.","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor op...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business professor. The professor gave the following message.","DataExportTag":"Q167","QuestionID":"QID167"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID844","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Blockbuster failed to p...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Blockbuster failed to predict changes in industry trends and went bankrupt. Blockbuster CEO John Antioco had seen many fads rise and fall in his time. He was also an avid surfer and was fond of saying \u201cNo matter the ups and downs, you have to ride the wave.\u201d\r\n<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Blockbuster failed to p...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q844","QuestionID":"QID844"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID552","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\nThe damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. \nAn employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThe damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. \r\nAn employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q552","QuestionID":"QID552"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID566","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\nThey solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThey solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q566","QuestionID":"QID566"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID661","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\nThe damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. \nAn employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Con