ortantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThey solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q665","QuestionID":"QID665"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID814","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><i><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged. They solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q814","QuestionID":"QID814"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID820","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged. The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. An employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Dutch bicycle manufactu...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q820","QuestionID":"QID820"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID525","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q525","QuestionID":"QID525"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID539","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q539","QuestionID":"QID539"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID641","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br>\n<br>\n<i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q641","QuestionID":"QID641"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID657","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q657","QuestionID":"QID657"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID808","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q808","QuestionID":"QID808"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID838","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 2000, Blockbuster fa...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 2000, Blockbuster failed to predict the popularity of subscription based media in the future. Because of this, they rejected an offer to buy Netflix. As a result, when Netflix's subscription-based service became the most popular option for at home entertainment, Blockbuster went bankrupt.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. In 2000, Blockbuster fa...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q838","QuestionID":"QID838"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID826","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Merrick created a pet f...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Merrick created a pet food that reduced plaque. Yet, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure. This was particularly disappointing for Garth Merrick. In fact, this Texas-born CEO was so disappointed that he ate the unsold pet food for a month to punish himself. He became incredibly sick.\n<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Merrick created a pet f...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q826","QuestionID":"QID826"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID832","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Merrick created a pet f...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>Merrick created a pet food that reduced plaque. In their packaging, they advertised that the product would ensure pets had \u201cclean teeth.\u201d However, consumer reports showed that most customers were interested instead in foods that created \u201cfresh breath.\u201d Because of this small discrepancy, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. Merrick created a pet f...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q832","QuestionID":"QID832"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID129","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<br><br>The instructor gave this real-world case study.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q129","QuestionID":"QID129","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID213","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Sometimes it can be lucrative for a company to improve the simplicity and speed of delivery rather than improve the product itself.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor.<br><br>The instructor gave this real-world case study.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q213","QuestionID":"QID213"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID258","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q258","QuestionID":"QID258"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID339","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>The amount of products a company can introduce is limited by the mental associations customers have with its brand. Introducing a product that is very different from the rest probably won't work.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q339","QuestionID":"QID339"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID345","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Failing to take the necessary safety precautions before performing a dangerous operation can have disastrous consequences.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q345","QuestionID":"QID345"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID351","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Subtle differences in the description of a product\u2019s benefits can dramatically change a product\u2019s sales.\n<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q351","QuestionID":"QID351"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID417","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Sometimes it can be lucrative for a company to improve the simplicity and speed of delivery rather than improve the product itself.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q417","QuestionID":"QID417"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID437","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Sometimes it can be lucrative for a company to improve the simplicity and speed of delivery rather than improve the product itself.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q437","QuestionID":"QID437"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID457","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Failing to recognize and adapt to emerging industry trends can lead to missed opportunities and potential business failure.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Sometimes it can be lucrative for a company to improve the simplicity and speed of delivery rather than improve the product itself.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q457","QuestionID":"QID457"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID519","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q519","QuestionID":"QID519"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID546","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q546","QuestionID":"QID546"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID621","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence, people often require the support of an underlying theory before they will change their minds.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q621","QuestionID":"QID621"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID659","SecondaryAttribute":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor. The instructor gave thi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by an instructor.<\/b><br><br><b>The instructor gave this message.<\/b><br><br><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><br>","DataExportTag":"Q659","QuestionID":"QID659"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID83","SecondaryAttribute":"The information you were shown derives from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof f...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<i>The information you were shown derives from this case study:<br><\/i><br><b>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\n<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>The company came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found instantaneous results: shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q83","QuestionID":"QID83","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The information you were shown derives from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof f...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID470","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Blockbuster failed to predict changes in...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Blockbuster failed to predict changes in industry trends and went bankrupt. Blockbuster CEO John Antioco had seen many fads rise and fall in his time. He was also an avid  surfer and was fond of saying \u201cNo matter the ups and downs, you have to ride the wave.\u201d<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Blockbuster failed to predict changes in...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q470","QuestionID":"QID470"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID512","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle man...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle man...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new television.\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q512","QuestionID":"QID512"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID559","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle man...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle man...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q559","QuestionID":"QID559"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID663","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle man...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle man...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Companies (such as the Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof) that package their products (in this case high end bicycles that include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors) in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products (in this case printing an image of a television on the box) can reduce damages due to shipping (nobody wants to damage a new television).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q663","QuestionID":"QID663"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID357","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Dettol was a trusted antiseptic brand lo...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dettol was a trusted antiseptic brand looking to expand. Because of this, they introduced over 8 new products, including soap, shaving cream, floor cleaner, talcum powder, mouthwash, handwash, moisturizer, and sunscreen. Only the soap and handwash were successful, with the rest of the products hovering between 0.5% and 5% market share. Dettol could have prevented this poor investment by recognizing that people only associated the brand as being \u201ca germ killer,\u201d and \u201cdoctor\u2019s choice.\u201d<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Dettol was a trusted antiseptic brand lo...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q357","QuestionID":"QID357"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID423","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThe damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some include delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. \r\nAn employee offered a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting TVs, shipping damages dropped. Nobody wants to damage a new TV.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q423","QuestionID":"QID423"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID430","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.\r\nThey solved the problem in a clever way. It all started when the CEO decided to read through the list of customer complaints. One evening, he was struck by one of the messages complaining about damaged bikes. Something about the tone of the message seemed very familiar. The CEO reached out to this customer and discovered that they had a lot in common. For one, they were both CEOs. But, more importantly, they were long lost brothers, separated from a very early age. Together, they came up with a solution to the shipping problem and forged a new bond.\r\n\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q430","QuestionID":"QID430"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID484","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Even if you have extremely compelling ev...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Even if you have extremely compelling ev...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q484","QuestionID":"QID484"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID532","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Even if you have extremely compelling ev...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Even if you have extremely compelling ev...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q532","QuestionID":"QID532"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID655","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Even if you have extremely compelling ev...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Even if you have extremely compelling ev...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Even if you have extremely compelling evidence (like Dr. Semmelweis\u2019s experiments which proved that hospitals which had higher death rates had doctors who were not washing their hands), people often require the support of an underlying theory (in this case germ theory) before they will change their minds (in this case, deciding to universally wash hands).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q655","QuestionID":"QID655"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID505","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Failing to recognize and adapt to emergi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Failing to recognize and adapt to emerging industry trends (such as Blockbuster failing to predict the popularity of subscription-based media) can lead to missed opportunities (in this case Blockbuster rejecting an offer to buy Netflix) and potential business failure (in this case, Blockbuster going bankrupt).<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Failing to recognize and adapt to emergi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2000, Blockbuster failed to predict the popularity of subscription based-media in the future. Because of this, they rejected an offer to buy Netflix. As a result, when Netflix's subscription-based service became the most popular option for at home entertainment, Blockbuster went bankrupt.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q505","QuestionID":"QID505"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID498","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Failing to take the necessary safety pre...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Failing to take the necessary safety precautions (such as when OceanGate failed to get its submersible Titan certified by any regulatory authorities, and opted for a cheap carbon fiber hull over a material that was rated to survive at great depths) before performing a dangerous operation (in this case, exploring the wreckage of the Titanic) can have disastrous consequences (in this case, the carbon fiber hull collapsed and all 5 people perished).<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Failing to take the necessary safety pre...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a submersible to explore the wreckage of the Titanic called \u201cTitan\u201d. The company ignored the advice of every deep sea diving expert and failed to get Titan certified by any regulatory authorities. They also opted for cheap materials when constructing the submersible \u2013 choosing carbon fiber over a material that was rated to survive at the depths of the Titanic, and a Playstation controller instead of the usual steering system. During the dive to the Titanic, the carbon fiber hull collapsed and all 5 crew members perished.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q498","QuestionID":"QID498"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID443","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q443","QuestionID":"QID443"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID450","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prov...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. But his ideas were rejected. Frustrated by this, he became increasingly paranoid and obsessive. In 1865, he was committed to a mental asylum, where he was beaten by guards. He died shortly afterward, possibly from sepsis. Ironically, his death was likely caused by the same lack of hygiene he had worked to correct.\r\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis was able to prov...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q450","QuestionID":"QID450"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID463","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2000, Blockbuster failed to predict t...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2000, Blockbuster failed to predict the popularity of subscription based-media in the future. Because of this, they rejected an offer to buy Netflix. As a result, when Netflix's subscription-based service became the most popular option for at home entertainment, Blockbuster went bankrupt.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2000, Blockbuster failed to predict t...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q463","QuestionID":"QID463"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID396","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2008, a local pizza joint was sufferi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, a local pizza joint was suffering from the Great Recession and the local consensus was that their delivery service was slow and annoying. Instead of hiring more bicycle delivery people, they decided to hire more car delivery people. Customers now got their pizza much faster. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their profits rose significantly.<br><\/i><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2008, a local pizza joint was sufferi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a sales system that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers could customize their pizza online or through an app, and save their preferences. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose from $2.83 to $433.78.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q396","QuestionID":"QID396"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID477","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2008, a local pizza joint was sufferi...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, a local pizza joint was suffering from the Great Recession and the local consensus was that their delivery service was slow and annoying. Instead of hiring more bicycle delivery people, they decided to hire more car delivery people. Customers now got their pizza much faster. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their profits rose significantly.<br><\/i><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2008, a local pizza joint was sufferi...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, a local pizza joint was suffering from the Great Recession and the local consensus was that their delivery service was slow and annoying. Instead of hiring more bicycle delivery people, they decided to hire more car delivery people. Customers now got their pizza much faster. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their profits rose significantly.<br><\/i><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q477","QuestionID":"QID477"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID288","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the Great Recession and the general consensus that their pizza was low quality. Instead of improving their pizza, they created a mobile app that optimized ordering and delivery. Customers now got their pizza much faster. Because of this, from 2008 to 2020 their stock rose significantly.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In 2008, Dominos was suffering from the...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The following information was taken from a lesson given by a business instructor. <br><br>The instructor gave this message.<\/b>","DataExportTag":"Q288","QuestionID":"QID288"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID371","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a subm...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a submersible to explore the wreckage of the Titanic called \u201cTitan\u201d. The company ignored the advice of every deep sea diving expert and failed to get Titan certified by any regulatory authorities. They also opted for cheap materials when constructing the submersible \u2013 choosing carbon fiber over a material that was rated to survive at the depths of the Titanic, and a Playstation controller instead of the usual steering system. During the dive to the Titanic, the carbon fiber hull collapsed and all 5 crew members perished.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a subm...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q371","QuestionID":"QID371"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID403","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a subm...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a submersible called \u201cTitan\u201d to explore the wreckage of the Titanic. Aboard its first descent was Stockton Rush, the company\u2019s ambitious leader. From a young age, Rush had been interested in exploring distant frontiers \u2013 from the starry heavens to the murky depths. Now he finally had a vessel that could do it. He boarded Titan for its maiden voyage, and rode it to the depth of the Titanic. With the famous sunken ship finally in view, Rush was about to take his first look. But then Titan collapsed, crushing him and his crew instantly. <\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: In the 2010s, OceanGate developed a subm...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 2007, A Korean telecommunications company wanted to make an expensive move from 2G to 3G, but 3G only offered video-calling, roaming, and slightly higher speed data over competitors. To generate customer interest, they branded 3G around these features as \u201cthe key to fun.\u201d Accordingly, they released a teaser ad called \u201cDeath of Boredom,\u201d recolored their stores in bright orange and white, and did a promotion with a major movie theater chain. As a result, the 3G transition brought 8.7 times the ad impact of its competitors, and increased their profits by $450 million in just 2007, despite pouring $2.8 billion into marketing.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q403","QuestionID":"QID403"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID364","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Merrick created a pet food that reduced...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Merrick created a pet food that reduced plaque. In their packaging, they advertised that the product would ensure pets had \u201cclean teeth.\u201d However, consumer reports showed that most customers were interested instead in foods that created \u201cfresh breath.\u201d Because of this small discrepancy, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure.\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Merrick created a pet food that reduced...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>In 1843, Dr. Semmelweis noticed a 3 to 1 imbalance in deaths due to childbirth at one hospital compared to another. He performed experiments and was able to prove that the problem was that doctors in one hospital were not washing their hands. He then showed the hospital his data, but no one listened. It was only with the widespread adoption of germ theory (decades later), which supported his findings that all doctors began washing hands.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q364","QuestionID":"QID364"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID410","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Merrick created a pet food that reduced...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Merrick created a pet food that reduced plaque. Yet, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure. This was particularly disappointing for Garth Merrick. This Texas-born CEO knew his product was of high quality. Legend revealed that he personally taste-tested each of the pet foods before they went out to market: if they were good enough for his customer\u2019s pets, they were good enough for him. <\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Merrick created a pet food that reduced...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Merrick created a pet food that reduced plaque. In their packaging, they advertised that the product would ensure pets had \u201cclean teeth.\u201d However, consumer reports showed that 54% - 59% of customers were interested instead in foods that created \u201cfresh breath.\u201d Because of this small discrepancy, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q410","QuestionID":"QID410"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID491","SecondaryAttribute":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Subtle differences in the description of...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Subtle differences in the description of a product\u2019s benefits (such as describing a pet food as ensuring \u201cclean teeth\u201d instead of \u201cfresh breath\u201d) can dramatically change a product\u2019s sales (in this case the pet food sales were a failure for the company Merrick).\n<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The message you were shown derived from this case study: Subtle differences in the description of...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"<b>The message you were shown derived from this case study:<\/b><br><br><i>Murrick created a detergent that would retain a fabric\u2019s appearance. In their packaging, they advertised that the product would ensure customers' clothing had \u201cless wrinkles.\u201d However, consumer reports showed that most customers were interested instead in clothing that had \u201cbrighter colors.\u201d Because of this small discrepancy, after a year, the product\u2019s sales were considered a company failure.<\/i><br><br><b>Now please rate this case study.<\/b><br>","DataExportTag":"Q491","QuestionID":"QID491"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID2","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case: Companies that package their pr...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"hypothetical","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor then state that this was the message from the case: Companies that package their pr...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID2"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID160","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. Please read it...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. <u>Please read it closely.<\/u><\/b><u><br><\/u><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to accompany the message with the following real-world case. Please read it...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q160","QuestionID":"QID160"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID132","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. Please read it...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"<b>The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. <u>Please read it closely.<\/u><\/b><br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"color:#2980b9;\"><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"DataExportTag":"Q132","QuestionID":"QID132","QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to accompany the real-world case with the following message. Please read it...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID143","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was: Companies that package their pr...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br>\n<br>\n<span style=\"color:#27ae60;\"><i>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<\/i><\/span>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was: Companies that package their pr...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message of this case was:<br><br>Companies that package their products in ways that superficially resemble those of more fragile products can reduce damages due to shipping.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q143","QuestionID":"QID143"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID176","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br><i>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<\/i><br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q176","QuestionID":"QID176"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID200","SecondaryAttribute":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DefaultChoices":false,"QuestionType":"DB","Selector":"TB","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case: Dutch bicy...","ChoiceOrder":[],"Validation":{"Settings":{"Type":"None"}},"GradingData":[],"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"The professor went on to state that the message was derived from this real-world case:<br><br>Dutch bicycle manufacturer VanMoof found that it had a problem. As it shipped its products to customers, it found that many bicycles were arriving to customers damaged.<br><br>The damage reports were a major problem for the company because the company\u2019s bikes are high-end, and some are loaded down with delicate electronics like anti-theft trackers and electric motors. Plus, the company had set a goal to sell 90 percent of its bikes online by the end of the decade.<br><br>One of the employees came up with a solution: print a graphic of a flatscreen television on the side of the box. By making shippers think that they were transporting flatscreen televisions, the company found that shipping damage dropped by 70-80 percent. Nobody wants to damage a new television.<br>","DataExportTag":"Q200","QuestionID":"QID200"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID97","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent could someone apply this information to other situations?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent could someone apply this information to other situations?","DataExportTag":"Q97","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAVR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent could someone apply this information to other situations?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 1"},"2":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 2"},"3":{"Display":"Click to write Choice 3"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"OFF","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":4,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID97"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID573","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","DataExportTag":"Q573","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Very little"},"3":{"Display":"A little"},"4":{"Display":"Somewhat"},"5":{"Display":"Moderately"},"6":{"Display":"A lot"},"7":{"Display":"A great deal"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4","5","6","7"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":8,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID573"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID618","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","DataExportTag":"mes.world.vien","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Barely"},"3":{"Display":"A little"},"4":{"Display":"Somewhat"},"5":{"Display":"Moderately"},"6":{"Display":"Very"},"7":{"Display":"Extremely"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4","5","6","7"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":8,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID618"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID626","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Completely useless"},"2":{"Display":"Almost useless"},"3":{"Display":"A little useful"},"4":{"Display":"Somewhat useful"},"5":{"Display":"Moderately useful"},"6":{"Display":"Very useful"},"7":{"Display":"Extremely useful"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4","5","6","7"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":8,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionText_Unsafe":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","DataExportTag":"Q626","QuestionID":"QID626"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID632","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","DataExportTag":"irr.world.vien","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Barely"},"3":{"Display":"A little"},"4":{"Display":"Somewhat"},"5":{"Display":"Moderately"},"6":{"Display":"Very"},"7":{"Display":"Extremely"}},"ChoiceOrder":["1","2","3","4","5","6","7"],"Validation":{"Settings":{"ForceResponse":"ON","ForceResponseType":"ON","Type":"None"}},"Language":[],"NextChoiceId":8,"NextAnswerId":1,"QuestionID":"QID632"}},{"SurveyID":"SV_6EI0MEnaSELekgS","Element":"SQ","PrimaryAttribute":"QID638","SecondaryAttribute":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","TertiaryAttribute":null,"Payload":{"QuestionText":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","DataExportTag":"nar.world.vien","QuestionType":"MC","Selector":"SAHR","SubSelector":"TX","DataVisibility":{"Private":false,"Hidden":false},"Configuration":{"QuestionDescriptionOption":"UseText","LabelPosition":"BELOW"},"QuestionDescription":"To what extent does this information enhance your understanding of how the world works?","Choices":{"1":{"Display":"Not at all"},"2":{"Display":"Barely"},"3":{"Display":"A little"},"4":{"Display":"Somewhat"},"5":{"Display":"Moderately"},"6":{"Display":"Very"},"7":{"Display":"Extremely"}},"Ch